subSubSection.paragraph:
Male genitalia
.

Median lobe (Fig. 
12
) short and stout, distinctly bent ventrally; apical orifice very long, stretching from basal bulb to apical lamella, not narrowed in middle; in dorsal view, left and right straightly converged to apex and rounded to base; apical lamella short, length half its basal width, apex slightly truncate, somewhat rounded; in lateral view, ventral margin straight, not expanded at the middle; apex slightly thickened, faintly bent ventrally at tip; left paramere (Fig. 
14
) large and round, apical membranous filament small; right paramere (Fig. 
13
) markedly styloid; strongly curved (the angle between basal and apical portions near 120°), slightly widened in middle, slightly narrowed apically, apex moderately thin.

This species is only known from Zham Town, Nyalam County, Xizang, China (Fig. 
15
). The only specimen was caught along road during day in a cloudy forest at 2163 m a.s.l. (Fig. 
17
).
